        <!-- Smiley shapes are created with Past2Xaml application with converting Windings font symbols into customly sized Shapes data: -->
        <!-- 1) Open Word (or almost any other drawing application and add one smiley from Windings font symbols -->
        <!-- 2) Copy smiles character to clipboard -->
        <!-- 3) Open Past2Xaml application (make sure Auto Size objects checkbox is checked) -->
        <!-- 4) Click paste button (the third on the left bottom) to display the copied shape in Past2Xaml (behind the scenes the Ab2d.ReaderWmf library converted the smiley in metafile format into WPF shapes) -->
        <!-- 5) In export options select "Get geometries" and for "Export Text as" select "Path geometry" -->
        <!-- 5) Optionally you can also specify the target application with changing the "Export as" and specify Silverlight or WinRT -->
        <!-- 6) You can also resize the path data to any size with "Change size" section - for example for Feedback control we changed size to specify 22 as new height  -->
        <!-- 7) Copy the value the Geometry property (string with "F1..." from GeometryDrawing element into XAML -->
